# SiteSyncAI — Product Vision

## What We Are Building

SiteSyncAI is the construction operating system that makes every platform that came before it look like it was built in 2005.

We are not improving on Procore. We are making Procore irrelevant.

The construction industry runs on $2 trillion of projects per year. It runs on phone calls, emails, paper, and software that was designed for the way people worked in 2010. The superintendent who manages a $200M tower is still using tools that treat them like a data entry clerk. That ends here.

SiteSyncAI is AI-native, field-first, and built like a tech titan would build it if they actually understood construction. Every workflow is faster, smarter, and more intuitive than anything that exists today. The AI is not a chatbot in a sidebar. It is woven into every action, every page, every decision.

## Who Uses It

**The Superintendent.** On the job site at 6am. iPhone in hand. Dusty gloves. Does not have time to navigate 8 tabs. Needs to log daily work, capture issues, and communicate with the office in under 3 minutes. If the software slows them down, they will not use it.

**The Project Manager.** Responsible for schedule, budget, RFIs, submittals, and subcontractor coordination simultaneously. Needs total visibility and total control. Needs AI that tells them what is about to go wrong before it does.

**The CFO or Owner.** Needs real numbers, not sanitized reports. Cash flow, retainage, committed costs, projected final cost. Real time. Trusted. Exportable for the board deck.

**The General Contractor executive.** Running 20 projects across 5 states. Needs portfolio-level visibility that rolls up in real time. Needs to know which jobs are healthy and which need attention, without reading 20 status reports.

## What It Must Feel Like

Walking into the best-run job site you have ever seen. Everything in its place. Everyone knows what they need to know. Problems surface before they become crises. The AI is like having the best project engineer you have ever worked with, always available, never wrong about the facts.

On mobile it must feel like the best iPhone app ever built for construction. Fast. Intuitive. Works offline. Looks like it was designed by Apple.

On desktop it must feel like Linear, Figma, or Stripe. Keyboard shortcuts everywhere. Instant feedback. Data that tells a story at a glance.

## The North Star Features

These are the things that will make a $500M GC switch overnight and never look back:

1. **AI that catches problems before they become delays.** It reads the schedule, the weather, the RFI log, the delivery schedule, and tells you on Monday morning what is going to go wrong on Thursday. Not after it happens.

2. **Financial visibility that goes from contract to cash in 3 clicks.** AIA billing, job costing, cash flow forecasting, retainage tracking, lien waivers. All of it connected, all of it real-time. A CFO can close the books faster because the data is already there.

3. **Field capture so fast a super will actually use it.** One-tap daily log. Voice to text. Photo with AI tagging. QR code crew check-in. Done in under 90 seconds.

4. **An RFI workflow that does not feel like paperwork.** Create, route, respond, close. The AI drafts the response. The design team gets it instantly. No email chains. No lost threads.

5. **A schedule that knows when it is wrong.** Baseline vs actual. AI-predicted completion dates based on real productivity data. Recovery plan suggestions when phases slip.

## What We Are NOT Building

- Another feature-dumped enterprise app that requires a 3-day training and a dedicated admin
- A Procore clone with a fresh coat of paint
- Software that ignores how construction actually works in the field
- A tool that only works if you have a perfect internet connection
- A platform that treats the superintendent as a second-class user

## How SiteSync Should Evolve

The engine that runs overnight should push the platform toward things that have never been done in construction software. Not just fixing bugs or adding standard features. Inventing new categories.

Examples of what invention looks like:

- A predictive labor analytics engine that forecasts crew productivity based on weather, day of week, and historical data for each trade
- An AI that monitors drawing revisions and automatically flags which RFIs, submittals, and change orders are affected
- A lien waiver tracker that automatically generates and routes conditional/unconditional waivers based on pay app approvals
- A real-time subcontractor scorecard that tracks on-time delivery, quality, safety incidents, and RFI response time across all projects in the portfolio
- A cash flow engine that models 13-week cash flow from committed costs, approved pay apps, pending change orders, and known upcoming payments
- An AI site visitor that can answer an owner's question about their project by reading all the project data and giving them a plain-English answer

## The Standard We Hold Ourselves To

Every UI decision: would Apple ship this?
Every workflow decision: would a superintendent actually use this on a job site?
Every data decision: would a CFO trust these numbers to present to a board?
Every AI decision: does this actually help, or does it just look impressive?

If the answer to any of those is no, we go back and fix it.

## The Competitive Bar

We are ahead of Procore, Autodesk Construction Cloud, Fieldwire, Buildertrend, and CoConstruct across every dimension that matters to a $50M+ GC. Not slightly ahead. Categorically ahead. The way iPhone was ahead of Nokia in 2007.

This is the only acceptable outcome.
